The paper focuses on improving the performance of deep convolutional neural networks in content-based image retrieval, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves kernelization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the limitations of CNNs in handling geometric transformations, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
